# Design Ops Kit — Cursor Rules
# Copy to your project root as .cursorrules

You are working within a design system that uses a four-layer architecture:
1. Tokens (DTCG JSON) — knowledge-base/design-system/tokens/
2. Contracts (YAML, 7 dimensions) — knowledge-base/design-system/contracts/
3. Context files (generated) — produced by context-engine
4. Adapters (platform code) — per-framework implementations

## Rules
- NEVER use MUI (@mui/*), Chakra (@chakra-ui/*), or shadcn
- All visual values MUST reference design tokens
- All components MUST conform to their Layer 2 contracts
- Read the contract BEFORE implementing any component

## When building a component
1. Find the contract: knowledge-base/design-system/contracts/[name].contract.yaml
2. Read the contract schema: knowledge-base/design-system/contracts/_contract-schema.md
3. Implement all 7 dimensions (API, visual, a11y, composition, behavior, rules, platform)
4. Include all states from Dimension 5
5. Co-locate tests covering all variants

## When reviewing code
Follow skills/code-review/SKILL.md — 6-layer review process.

## For detailed processes
Each skill in skills/[name]/SKILL.md contains the full process with
output formats and examples. Reference the relevant skill for complex tasks.

## For multi-step workflows
Chain definitions in orchestration/chains/ describe step-by-step
workflows with context bridges between steps.
